{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864921324,"sessionID":"ses_28633fc56ffeCSwv35RvkQw1Ey","part":{"id":"prt_d79cc2651001qdshxKdUlF0SSO","messageID":"msg_d79cc193c001A6OC9BeO9spr0g","sessionID":"ses_28633fc56ffeCSwv35RvkQw1Ey","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012 Design Document\n2: \n3: ## 会话存储接口定义\n4: \n5: ## Overview\n6: \n7: (TBD - Design to be completed)\n8: \n9: ## Interface Design\n10: \n11: (TBD)\n12: \n13: ## Data Model\n14: \n15: (TBD)\n16: \n17: ## Error Handling\n18: \n19: (TBD)\n20: \n21: ## Implementation Notes\n22: \n23: (TBD)\n\n(End of file - total 23 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012 Design Document\n\n## 会话存储接口定义\n\n## Overview\n\n(TBD - Design to be completed)\n\n## Interface Design\n\n(TBD)\n\n## Data Model\n\n(TBD)\n\n## Error Handling\n\n(TBD)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/design.md","time":{"start":1775864921286,"end":1775864921322}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864921327,"sessionID":"ses_28633fc56ffeCSwv35RvkQw1Ey","part":{"id":"prt_d79cc3159001h5gZKra0W8eO4f","messageID":"msg_d79cc193c001A6OC9BeO9spr0g","sessionID":"ses_28633fc56ffeCSwv35RvkQw1Ey","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012: 会话存储接口定义 (Session Store Interface Definition) - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-012  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: **Base Spec:** [session-store/design.md](../../session-store/design.md), [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n10: \n11: The Session Store Interface provides a unified storage abstraction for persisting sandbox session metadata, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. It enables CRUD operations on sandbox information, indexes sessions by expiry and last activity times for garbage collection, and provides a thread-safe singleton access pattern.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods for session management.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Store interface methods\n22: - **GIVEN** a `Store` implementation (Redis or Valkey)\n23: - **WHEN** the interface is used\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL provide:\n25:   - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` - verify connectivity\n26:   - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - retrieve sandbox\n27:   - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` - create new sandbox\n28:   - `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` - update existing sandbox\n29:   - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error` - delete sandbox\n30:   - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - list expired\n31:   - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` - list inactive\n32:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` - update activity timestamp\n33:   - `Close() error` - close the store connection\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n36: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n37: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n38: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n39: - **AND** returns nil error on success\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Ping fails on unhealthy server\n42: - **GIVEN** an unreachable or unhealthy Redis/Valkey server\n43: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n44: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n49: \n50: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when operations target a missing session.\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n53: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` exists in the backend\n54: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"unknown-session\")` is called\n55: - **THEN** the returned error SHALL be `ErrNotFound`\n56: - **AND** the result SHALL be nil\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Redis nil error translates to ErrNotFound\n59: - **GIVEN** a Redis backend\n60: - **AND** a non-existent session key\n61: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` returns `redis.Nil`\n62: - **THEN** the error SHALL be converted to `ErrNotFound`\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Valkey nil error translates to ErrNotFound\n65: - **GIVEN** a Valkey backend\n66: - **AND** a non-existent session key\n67: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` returns `IsValkeyNil` response\n68: - **THEN** the error SHALL be converted to `ErrNotFound`\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Update activity on missing session returns ErrNotFound\n71: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists\n72: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"missing-id\", now)` is called\n73: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`\n74: - **AND** SHALL NOT modify any ZSET indexes\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ### Requirement: Session Key Naming\n79: \n80: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Key construction for session\n83: - **GIVEN** a session id `abc123`\n84: - **WHEN** the store writes or reads sandbox data\n85: - **THEN** the string key SHALL be `session:abc123`\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Key construction with special characters\n88: - **GIVEN** a session id containing special characters like `sess-123_test.abc`\n89: - **WHEN** the store constructs the key\n90: - **THEN** the key SHALL be `session:sess-123_test.abc`\n91: - **AND** the session id SHALL be preserved exactly\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: Expiry Index Management\n96: \n97: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds for garbage collection.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n100: - **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` and `ExpiresAt=time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n101: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n102: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZADD session:expiry 1234567890 sess-1`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from expiry index\n105: - **GIVEN** an existing session in the expiry index\n106: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n107: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZREM session:expiry sess-1`\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n110: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n111: - **AND** `before` timestamp is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n112: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n113: - **THEN** it SHALL select members with scores from negative infinity through `1234567890`\n114: - **AND** limit results to `limit` entries\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes with limit <= 0 returns empty\n117: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` or negative limit\n118: - **WHEN** the method is called\n119: - **THEN** it SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying the backend\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes loads full documents\n122: - **GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session ids `[\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\"]`\n123: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` continues processing\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL fetch the full JSON documents for each session id\n125: - **AND** return a slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ### Requirement: Last-Activity Index Management\n130: \n131: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds.\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to activity index with current time\n134: - **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n135: - **AND** current time is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n136: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n137: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZADD session:last_activity 1234567890 sess-1`\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity updates activity index\n140: - **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n141: - **AND** update time `at = time.Unix(1234567900, 0)`\n142: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", at)` is called\n143: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZADD session:last_activity 1234567900 sess-1`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity with zero time uses now\n146: - **GIVEN** an existing session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n147: - **AND** `at` is zero time (`time.Time{}`)\n148: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", at)` is called\n149: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `time.Now().Unix()` as the score\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from activity index\n152: - **GIVEN** an existing session in the activity index\n153: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n154: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1`\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n157: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n158: - **AND** `before` timestamp is `time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n159: - **WHEN** executed\n160: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `1234567890` SHALL be returned up to `limit`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes with limit <= 0 returns empty\n163: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)`\n164: - **WHEN** the method is called\n165: - **THEN** it SHALL return `nil, nil` without querying the backend\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox Atomicity and Validation\n170: \n171: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n174: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n175: - **WHEN** called\n176: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n177: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis/Valkey commands\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n180: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}`\n181: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n182: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating invalid expiry\n183: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis/Valkey commands\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Empty SessionID rejected\n186: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n187: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n188: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating invalid session ID\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n191: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox to store\n192: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is executed\n193: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute in a single pipeline/multi:\n194:   - `SETNX session:{id} {json}`\n195:   - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_at_unix} {id}`\n196:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} {id}`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Pipeline failure returns error\n199: - **GIVEN** any command in the StoreSandbox pipeline fails\n200: - **WHEN** execution completes\n201: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error\n202: - **AND** partial writes SHALL NOT occur (atomic operation)\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n207: \n208: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries.\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox modifies only session data\n211: - **GIVEN** an existing session with updated sandbox info\n212: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called\n213: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute `SET session:{id} {json} XX`\n214: - **AND** SHALL NOT modify `session:expiry` ZSET\n215: - **AND** SHALL NOT modify `session:last_activity` ZSET\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Missing key on update returns error\n218: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n219: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs on Redis\n220: - **THEN** SET with XX returns nil\n221: - **AND** the system SHALL return error `key not exists`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Missing key on update returns error (Valkey)\n224: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n225: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs on Valkey\n226: - **THEN** if response is not \"OK\"\n227: - **AND** the system SHALL return error indicating key does not exist\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox on update rejected\n230: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n231: - **WHEN** called\n232: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n237: \n238: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: Full removal cleanup\n241: - **GIVEN** an existing session `sess-1`\n242: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` succeeds\n243: - **THEN** `GET session:sess-1` SHALL return not found\n244: - **AND** `session:expiry` ZSET SHALL NOT contain `sess-1`\n245: - **AND** `session:last_activity` ZSET SHALL NOT contain `sess-1`\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Delete executes in atomic pipeline\n248: - **GIVEN** an existing session to delete\n249: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` is called\n250: - **THEN** the system SHALL execute in a single pipeline/multi:\n251:   - `DEL session:{id}`\n252:   - `ZREM session:expiry {id}`\n253:   - `ZREM session:last_activity {id}`\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Empty session ID returns error\n256: - **GIVEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")`\n257: - **WHEN** called\n258: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating invalid session ID\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ### Requirement: List Loaders Tolerate Missing Keys\n263: \n264: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing without failing the whole batch.\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member is skipped\n267: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a corresponding string value\n268: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n269: - **THEN** that id SHALL be omitted from the returned slice\n270: - **AND** the operation SHALL continue with other valid sessions\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Redis pipeline GET nil handling\n273: - **GIVEN** Redis pipeline GET returns nil for some keys\n274: - **WHEN** processing list results\n275: - **THEN** nil results SHALL be filtered out\n276: - **AND** only valid sandbox documents SHALL be returned\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Valkey MGET empty string handling\n279: - **GIVEN** Valkey MGET returns empty string for missing keys\n280: - **WHEN** processing list results\n281: - **THEN** empty results SHALL be filtered out\n282: - **AND** only valid sandbox documents SHALL be returned\n283: \n284: ---\n285: \n286: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n287: \n288: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: Empty session ID rejected\n291: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", now)`\n292: - **WHEN** called\n293: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating invalid session ID\n294: - **AND** SHALL NOT query the backend\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session returns ErrNotFound\n297: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists\n298: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"unknown-id\", now)` is called\n299: - **THEN** after existence check fails\n300: - **AND** the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`\n301: - **AND** SHALL NOT update the activity index\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: Zero time defaults to now\n304: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", time.Time{})`\n305: - **AND** session key exists\n306: - **WHEN** called\n307: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `time.Now().Unix()` as the ZADD score\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Provider Selection via STORE_TYPE\n312: \n313: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Default to Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n316: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n317: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n318: - **THEN** the Redis implementation SHALL be constructed\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Case-insensitive Redis selection\n321: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=REDIS` (uppercase)\n322: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n323: - **THEN** the Redis implementation SHALL be constructed\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Case-insensitive Valkey selection\n326: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=Valkey` (mixed case)\n327: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n328: - **THEN** the Valkey implementation SHALL be constructed\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE fails\n331: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=invalid`\n332: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n333: - **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with an error indicating unsupported store type\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ### Requirement: Redis Environment and Password Policy\n338: \n339: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n342: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n343: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n344: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n345: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n346: - **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with error indicating password is required\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Password can be disabled\n349: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n350: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n351: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive)\n352: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n353: - **THEN** initialization SHALL succeed with empty password\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: Missing REDIS_ADDR fails\n356: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is not set\n357: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n358: - **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with error indicating address is required\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: Case-insensitive password required flag\n361: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=FALSE`\n362: - **WHEN** checking password requirement\n363: - **THEN** the system SHALL treat it as disabled (case-insensitive compare to \"false\")\n364: \n365: ---\n366: \n367: ### Requirement: Valkey Environment and Options\n368: \n369: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Parse comma-separated Valkey addresses\n372: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=valkey1:6379,valkey2:6379,valkey3:6379`\n373: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n374: - **THEN** `InitAddress` SHALL be `[\"valkey1:6379\", \"valkey2:6379\", \"valkey3:6379\"]`\n375: \n376: #### Scenario: DisableCache when VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true\n377: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n378: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n379: - **THEN** `DisableCache` SHALL be true on `ClientOption`\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: DisableCache when VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=1\n382: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=1`\n383: - **WHEN** parsing the option\n384: - **THEN** `DisableCache` SHALL be true (ParseBool accepts \"1\" as true)\n385: \n386: #### Scenario: ForceSingleClient when VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true\n387: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n388: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n389: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` SHALL be true on `ClientOption`\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n392: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n393: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n394: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n395: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\n396: - **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with error indicating password is required\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: Valkey password can be disabled\n399: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:6379`\n400: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n401: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\n402: - **THEN** initialization SHALL succeed\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Missing VALKEY_ADDR fails\n405: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\n406: - **AND** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n407: - **WHEN** store initializes\n408: - **THEN** initialization SHALL fail with error indicating address is required\n409: \n410: ---\n411: \n412: ### Requirement: Singleton Access Pattern\n413: \n414: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n415: \n416: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n417: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently\n418: - **WHEN** they execute\n419: - **THEN** `initStore` SHALL execute exactly once\n420: - **AND** all goroutines SHALL receive the same Store instance\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: Successful init returns same instance\n423: - **GIVEN** `Storage()` has been called once successfully\n424: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called again\n425: - **THEN** the same Store instance SHALL be returned\n426: - **AND** initialization logic SHALL NOT re-execute\n427: \n428: #### Scenario: Failed init logs fatal\n429: - **GIVEN** store initialization fails (e.g., missing required env var)\n430: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n431: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`\n432: - **AND** the program SHALL terminate\n433: \n434: ---\n435: \n436: ### Requirement: Store Close Behavior\n437: \n438: The system SHALL properly close store connections and release resources.\n439: \n440: #### Scenario: Close releases Redis connection\n441: - **GIVEN** a Redis store instance with an active connection\n442: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n443: - **THEN** the underlying Redis client SHALL be closed\n444: - **AND** subsequent operations SHALL fail with connection errors\n445: \n446: #### Scenario: Close releases Valkey connection\n447: - **GIVEN** a Valkey store instance with an active connection\n448: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n449: - **THEN** the underlying Valkey client SHALL be closed\n450: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil on success\n451: \n452: ---\n453: \n454: ## Changes to Base Specification\n455: \n456: No modifications to existing interfaces. This AR introduces new storage capabilities for session management.\n457: \n458: ---\n459: \n460: ## New Interfaces\n461: \n462: ### Store Interface\n463: \n464: ```go\n465: package store\n466: \n467: import (\n468:     \"context\"\n469:     \"time\"\n470: \n471:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n472: )\n473: \n474: // Store defines the interface for session storage operations.\n475: type Store interface {\n476:     // Ping verifies connectivity to the storage backend.\n477:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n478: \n479:     // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox info by session ID.\n480:     // Returns ErrNotFound if the session does not exist.\n481:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n482: \n483:     // StoreSandbox creates a new sandbox entry with atomic index updates.\n484:     // Validates sandbox is non-nil and has valid ExpiresAt.\n485:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n486: \n487:     // UpdateSandbox updates an existing sandbox's JSON data.\n488:     // Uses SET with XX flag (key must exist).\n489:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n490: \n491:     // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes a sandbox and its indexes.\n492:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n493: \n494:     // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sessions with ExpiresAt <= before.\n495:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n496: \n497:     // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sessions with last activity <= before.\n498:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n499: \n500:     // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a session.\n501:     // Returns ErrNotFound if session does not exist.\n502:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n503: \n504:     // Close closes the store connection.\n505:     Close() error\n506: }\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ### Errors\n510: \n511: ```go\n512: // ErrNotFound is returned when a session key is not found.\n513: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n514: ```\n515: \n516: ### Provider Type Constants\n517: \n518: ```go\n519: const (\n520:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n521:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n522: )\n523: ```\n524: \n525: ### Singleton Access\n526: \n527: ```go\n528: // Storage returns the singleton Store instance.\n529: // Panics via klog.Fatal if initialization fails.\n530: func Storage() Store\n531: ```\n532: \n533: ---\n534: \n535: ## Modified Interfaces\n536: \n537: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Behavioral Changes\n542: \n543: | Behavior | Before | After |\n544: |----------|--------|-------|\n545: | Session persistence | Not available | Redis/Valkey backed storage |\n546: | Expiry tracking | Not available | ZSET index `session:expiry` for GC |\n547: | Activity tracking | Not available | ZSET index `session:last_activity` for idle detection |\n548: | Store provider | None | Configurable via `STORE_TYPE` env var |\n549: | Store access | None | Singleton pattern via `Storage()` |\n550: | Connection pooling | None | Managed by Redis/Valkey client libraries |\n551: \n552: ---\n553: \n554: ## Dependencies\n555: \n556: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n557: |------------|---------|---------|\n558: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.x | Redis client for Go |\n559: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Latest | Valkey client for Go |\n560: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n561: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | SandboxInfo type definition |\n562: \n563: ---\n564: \n565: ## File Index\n566: \n567: | Path | Purpose |\n568: |------|---------|\n569: | `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface definition and ErrNotFound |\n570: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Singleton Storage() access and provider selection |\n571: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation of Store interface |\n572: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation of Store interface |\n573: \n574: ---\n575: \n576: ## Constants\n577: \n578: | Constant | Value | Description |\n579: |----------|-------|-------------|\n580: | `redisStoreType` | `\"redis\"` | Redis provider type identifier |\n581: | `valkeyStoreType` | `\"valkey\"` | Valkey provider type identifier |\n582: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Key prefix for session data |\n583: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET key for expiry tracking |\n584: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET key for activity tracking |\n585: \n586: ---\n587: \n588: ## Environment Variables\n589: \n590: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n591: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n592: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Store provider: `redis` or `valkey` |\n593: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes* | - | Redis server address |\n594: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Redis authentication password |\n595: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n596: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes** | - | Comma-separated Valkey addresses |\n597: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes** | - | Valkey authentication password |\n598: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n599: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client cache |\n600: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` for single client mode |\n601: \n602: *Required when `STORE_TYPE=redis`  \n603: **Required when `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n604: \n605: ---\n606: \n607: ## API Endpoints Summary\n608: \n609: This AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n610: \n611: | Consumer | Usage |\n612: |----------|-------|\n613: | Session Manager | Persist and retrieve sandbox session metadata |\n614: | Idle Cleanup | Query inactive/expired sessions for garbage collection |\n615: | Session Router | Update activity timestamps on session access |\n616: \n617: ---\n618: \n619: ## Migration Notes\n620: \n621: - **New dependencies**: Add `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` and/or `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` to go.mod\n622: - **Environment setup**: Configure `REDIS_ADDR` or `VALKEY_ADDR` before deployment\n623: - **RBAC**: No Kubernetes RBAC requirements for this component\n624: - **Data format**: SandboxInfo is stored as JSON; ensure `pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo` is stable\n625: - **Index management**: The store manages ZSET indexes automatically; no manual migration needed\n626: \n627: ---\n628: \n629: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n630: \n631: 1. **Interface Contract**: All Store methods are implemented for both Redis and Valkey backends\n632: 2. **Key Naming**: Session keys use `session:{id}` format consistently\n633: 3. **Index Management**: Expiry and activity ZSETs are maintained correctly\n634: 4. **Error Handling**: `ErrNotFound` is returned for missing sessions; other errors are descriptive\n635: 5. **Atomicity**: StoreSandbox and DeleteSandboxBySessionID use atomic pipeline operations\n636: 6. **Provider Selection**: `STORE_TYPE` correctly selects between Redis and Valkey implementations\n637: 7. **Environment Validation**: Required environment variables are validated at initialization\n638: 8. **Singleton Pattern**: `Storage()` provides thread-safe singleton access\n639: 9. **Resource Cleanup**: `Close()` properly releases backend connections\n640: 10. **Orphan Tolerance**: List operations gracefully handle orphaned ZSET entries\n\n(End of file - total 640 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012: 会话存储接口定义 (Session Store Interface Definition) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-012  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [session-store/design.md](../../session-store/design.md), [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n\nThe Session Store Interface provides a unified storage abstraction for persisting sandbox session metadata, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. It enables CRUD operations on sandbox information, indexes sessions by expiry and last activity times for garbage collection, and provides a thread-safe singleton access pattern.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods for session management.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864921291,"end":1775864921325}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864921329,"sessionID":"ses_28633fc56ffeCSwv35RvkQw1Ey","part":{"id":"prt_d79cc2bd40011CL4VxDaZ5Vdlt","messageID":"msg_d79cc193c001A6OC9BeO9spr0g","sessionID":"ses_28633fc56ffeCSwv35RvkQw1Ey","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-012\n2: title: 会话存储接口定义\n3: module: pkg/store\n4: language: Go\n5: size: S\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n9: # Module: pkg/store\n10: # Language: Go\n11: # Size: S\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: session-storage-interface\n21:   description: |\n22:     Define the session storage interface for the agentcube project.\n23:     This interface abstracts the storage operations for session data,\n24:     providing a clean contract for session persistence and retrieval.\n25: \n26: # Scope\n27: scope:\n28:   in:\n29:     - Session storage interface definition\n30:     - CRUD operations for session data\n31:     - Interface abstractions for different storage backends\n32:     - Error handling contracts\n33:   out:\n34:     - Concrete storage implementations (separate AR)\n35:     - Migration logic (separate AR)\n36:     - Caching layer (separate AR)\n37: \n38: # Acceptance Criteria\n39: acceptance:\n40:   - Interface defines clear CRUD operations for sessions\n41:   - Interface is agnostic to storage backend\n42:   - Error types are well-defined\n43:   - Documentation is complete\n44:   - Unit tests for interface contracts\n45: \n46: # References\n47: references:\n48:   - AR-010: Router 会话管理\n49: \n50: # Estimation\n51: estimation:\n52:   size: S\n53:   story_points: 2\n54:   days: 1\n\n(End of file - total 54 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-012\ntitle: 会话存储接口定义\nmodule: pkg/store\nlanguage: Go\nsize: S\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n# Module: pkg/store\n# Language: Go\n# Size: S\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: session-storage-interface","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-012/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775864921289,"end":1775864921327}}}}
